     <h1 class="projectHeader" style="color: white; text-align: left;">About me</h1>
     <!--<hr style="border: solid #21c4d2; border-width: 1px; width: 10%; float: left;">-->
     <p style="color: white; text-align: left;"><br>My name is Viktor and i am currently studying for my bachelor degree in Interaction Design at
     Malmö Högskola. Right now, I am on my fourth semester with two to go. Since the field of Interaction Design is very broad
   we are given the opportunity to specialize in the area we find most interesting. For me it is programming. I studied one intro course of web development prior to Interaction Design which taught me the basics
of building websites, along with an intro course in C#. I have picked out several different projects I have worked in that I think represents me as an interaction designer. <br> <br><br>
<br>
I have always been fascinated by the technical evolution. Now I want to take part in making new technology more user friendly. <br><br>
       During our education, it is up to us students to decide what areas to focus on. This gives me a lot of opportunities to learn more
     about programming. In every project, I have had the role of lead developer. The main programming languages in the education is Java and JavaScript. Since web development
     is not a large part of my education, most of what I know about HTML, CSS and JavaScript is self-taught. I think of myself as an easy learner when it comes to programming and my goal is to work with front-end development.
     <br><br>Wellcome to my portfolio.
</p>
