          <iframe class="embed-responsive-item" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/yfcO9p3Xims" allowfullscreen></iframe>
          </div>
          </div>
            <div class="col-lg-6 col-xs-12 col-md-6 col-centered">
              <p class="modalText" style="color: black;">Ro is based on the charachsteristics of a spinning top. The game aims to let the player feel the same satisfaction
                one would get when spinning a physical top. The player picks up the digital artifact by touching it. A swing-motion will
                initialize the rotation of the orbs surounding the artifact. By letting go of the screen the player can controll the artifact
                by tilting the mobile device. Ro is made for mobile devices with Unity 3D. The game was user tested at an early stage, the end result is based on those tests.<br>
                My main task was programming the game.
              <br><br>
            Skills gained:<br>
                Learned basics within developing and testing mobile games in the unity engine<br>
                Got more experience with C#<br>
                A lot of practice working with user research</p>
            </div>
